====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|en|charme||obsolete}}

====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}

# An object, act or words believed to have [[magic]] [[power]] (usually carries a positive connotation).
#: ''a '''charm''' against evil''
#: ''It works like a '''charm'''.''
# The ability to [[persuade]], [[delight]] or arouse [[admiration]]; often constructed in the plural.
#: ''He had great personal '''charm'''.''
#: ''She tried to win him over with her '''charms'''.''
#* {{RQ:Pope Rape|year=1717|canto=V|passage='''Charms''' strike the sight, but merit wins the soul.}}
#* {{RQ:Milton PL|book=8|passage=the '''charm''' of beauty's powerful glance}}
# A small [[trinket]] on a [[bracelet]] or chain, etc., traditionally supposed to confer [[luck]] upon the wearer.
#: ''She wears a '''charm''' bracelet on her wrist.''
# {{lb|en|physics}} A [[quantum number]] of [[hadron|hadrons]] determined by the number of [[charm quark]]s and antiquarks.
# {{lb|en|finance}} A [[second-order]] measure of [[derivative]] price sensitivity, expressed as the instantaneous rate of change of [[delta]] with respect to time.

